page.title: 01General Review 1
page.content: The area surveyed comprises mostly Lytchett Matravers Parish together with parts of Morden, Sturminster Marshall and Corfe Mullen Parishes. There is no hamlet or village. It has a mainly north westerly aspect with views toward central Dorset. It is{sparsely populated {farmland}with areas of woodland. There is one large{mansion house, {Charborough,}and two smaller mansion houses, Henbury and Lytchett House. The Charborough estate still exists, but Henbury and Lytchett Matravers have been broken up and the lands sold. There are eight{farmhouses}with varying acreages; four farmhouses without lands; fifty-two other houses and cottages, and some small caravan homes.
